   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="calenderPage" n="1">
            <head>
               <date when="1909-03-11">March 11, 1909 (Thursday)</date>
            </head>
            <p>Everybody dressed in their best, For this is an Erie Tea- They eat too much, talk too
               much- You can bet they ain't safe in me. </p>
            <note> Maybe one of Mary's days to Sun!</note>
            <!--how to encode this so it mentions the text is red -->
            <figure>
               <figDesc> Four women in long formal dresses (lavender, vermillion, deep blue, sage)
               </figDesc>
            </figure>
         </div>

         <div type="calenderPage" n="2">
            <head>
               <date when="1909-03-12">March 12, 1909 (Friday)</date>
            </head>
            <p><name type="person">Molly</name> on snowshoes that <name type="person">Mr.Weir</name>
               got. Pretty picture is it not ?!</p>
            <note>Love from Molly.</note>
            <figure>
               <figDesc> A woman in a long winter coat with a bonnet walking on snow shoes.
               </figDesc>
            </figure>
         </div>
         <div type="calenderPage" n="3">
            <head>
               <date when="1909-03-17">March 17, 1909 (Wednesday - <name type="person">St. Patricks</name>'s Day)</date>
            </head>
            <p><name type="person">St. Patrick </name> was a usefuf saint. He Frightened all the
               snakes away- I wish He'd try his art on smoke - around the Hammermill some day!</p>
            <note>The Hammermill really needs brushing!</note>
            <figure>
               <figDesc> Two small snakes near the top of the page. A small sketch of the <name type= "place">Hammermill</name>
                  Factory surrounded by smoke.Four small green clovers decorate the page </figDesc>
            </figure>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
